President Obama has honored 108 mathematics and science teachers with the Presidential Award for Excellence in Mathematics and Science Teaching. The awardees represent all 50 states, the District of Columbia, Puerto Rico, U.S. Territories, and the Department of Defense Education Activity schools. The teachers will receive a $10,000 award from the National Science Foundation and will be invited to a ceremony in Washington, DC. President Obama emphasized the importance of math and science education in preparing the next generation for success in STEM fields. He has launched initiatives such as the "Educate to Innovate" campaign and the STEM Master Teacher Corps to support STEM education. The recipients of the Presidential Award for Excellence in Mathematics and Science Teaching are listed by state.